<p>I want to populate a select field with onclick but i don't know how to filter the array to only the value of the clicked button. With my code all the array objects populate the input and I want only the value of the clicked button to populate the input. Any hints?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="hidden" id="id_user" value="{{user.id}}"&gt;      &lt;select id="id_entities" class="js-example-programmatic" style="width:100%" multiple="multiple"&gt;     {% for teu in tagEntityUsers %}         &lt;option value="{{teu.entity_id}}" class="js-programmatic-set-val"&gt;{{teu.entity}}&lt;/option&gt;      {% endfor %}     &lt;/select&gt;   {% for teu in tagEntityUsers %}   &lt;tr&gt;     &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="/entities/{{teu.entity_id}}/{{teu.entity.slug}}"&gt;{{teu.entity}}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="{{ teu.user.get_absolute_url }}"&gt;{{teu.user}}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;td&gt;&lt;button id ="{{teu.entity_id}}" class="js-programmatic-set-val" value="{{teu.entity_id}}" onclick="populate_box(this.id)"&gt;add entity&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/td&gt;   &lt;/tr&gt;   {% endfor %}  &lt;script&gt; var $example = $(".js-example-programmatic"); var arr = $.map($('.js-programmatic-set-val'), function (el) { return el.value; }); function populate_box() {     $example.val(this.arr).trigger("change"); } &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>